block content
    h1 Sanelotto â€” deployment tool for any languages
    p Sanelotto developed for fast and simple deploy applications to server.
    p Sanelotto is suitable for any languages and any frameworks. Configuring is extremely simple - only need to change
        | JSON configuration files and enter the desired commands on the desired language.
    p After creating project you will get two directories - for local machine (usually virtual machine on Continuous
        | Integration service) and for server. During the update repository on GitHub local part make a SSH connection with
        | server part and update project on server.
    section.row
        article.col-md-6
            h2 Features
            ul
                li SSH connection through SSH-key or login/password
                li Four types custom commands: before connection, after first downloading, after updating, after first downloading and updating
                li Automatically overwriting chosen files
                li Optional detailed logging
        article.col-md-6
            h2 Benefits
            ul
                li Simple and fast
                li Multilanguage
                li Full Open Source
                li Crossplatform
                li For any CI services
                li Highly customizable through configuration files

    article.git_card
            .github-card(data-theme='medium', data-height='280', data-width='400', data-github='Vladimir37/Sanelotto')
            script(src='//cdn.jsdelivr.net/github-cards/latest/widget.js')